report.example.html is an example PDF fix list (originally produced for tmpc.org)
kept here as a design reference, NOT a template.

When building a new project's report:

1. Copy report.example.html into your audit repo's pdf-build/ as report.html
2. Replace ALL project-specific content (URLs, fix descriptions, screenshots, palette,
   typography choices) with content sourced from findings.json
3. Keep the page-break CSS rules intact — those are battle-tested and documented in
   SETUP.md Phase 3.4

The reusable parts:
  - CSS for page breaks, priority pills, callout boxes
  - 14-page structure: cover / overview / TOC / 10 fix pages / closing
  - Typography pairing (Fraunces + Inter, switchable)
  - Print-ready dimensions (8.5x11in with proper margins)

The non-reusable parts (replace per project):
  - Brand palette (CSS custom properties at top of <style>)
  - All page content
  - All URLs
  - Screenshots
